# Backend Development Rules

## Stack
Python 3.12, FastAPI, SQLAlchemy 2 (async), Alembic, Pydantic v2, scapy, python-jose (JWT), authlib (OAuth), httpx, OpenAI SDK, aiofiles, python-multipart, itsdangerous, psycopg2-binary (Alembic sync driver).

## Database
- All database access goes through `async_session` from `app.db.session`.
- Use the `async with async_session() as session:` pattern.
- Models live in `app/models/`, schemas in `app/schemas/`.
- `Base` is defined in `app.db.session`; import `app.models` to register all tables.
- Enum types use `str, enum.Enum` + `SAEnum` for PostgreSQL compatibility.
- Alembic migrations use a synchronous driver; `env.py` strips `+asyncpg`/`+psycopg_async` from `DATABASE_URL`.

## API Routes
- Prefixes: `/api/captures`, `/api/capture-command`, `/auth`, `/api/health`.
- Dependencies: `get_current_user` for auth; routes open their own `async_session()` context for DB access.
- Uploads: `POST /api/captures` — validates extensions (.pcap, .pcapng, .cap, plus tcpdump rotated suffixes like `.pcap0`) and pcap magic bytes, streams to a temp file, enforces `max_upload_bytes`, creates the DB record, and spawns `parse_pcap` as a background task.
- Captures: `GET /api/captures` lists with pagination; `GET /api/captures/{id}` reads one; `DELETE /api/captures/{id}` removes the DB row and best-effort filesystem sidecars (`.index.json`, `.jsonl`, `.summary.jsonl`, `.offsets.bin`) plus evicts the in-memory index AND proto-filter caches.
- Packets: `GET /api/captures/{id}/packets` reads `index.json`, supports `?proto=`, `?q=` (case-insensitive substring on src/dst/info/proto/app_proto), `?offset=`, `?limit=` (default 200, max 10000; filters apply to `total`). `GET /api/captures/{id}/packets/{packet_idx}` returns full detail from `.jsonl` and enriches each protocol-tree node with Wireshark-parity `fields` (name/value/offset/length) on demand. Enrichment is O(1): the packet is reconstructed from the stored `raw_hex` + the capture `linktype` via `packet_fields.packet_from_raw_hex` (scapy), with `read_packet_at` (full-pcap scan) only as a fallback when `raw_hex` is missing or dissection fails.
- Follow Stream: `GET /api/captures/{id}/follow` — reconstructs one TCP/UDP conversation's transport payload (query params `src_ip`, `src_port`, `dst_ip`, `dst_port`, `proto` ∈ {tcp,udp}); re-reads the pcap in a worker thread; payload capped at 1 MB per direction; returns base64 segments split by client/server direction.
- Export: `GET /api/captures/{id}/export?format=csv|json` — streams the (optionally `proto`/`q`-filtered) packet list as CSV or JSON; uses a sync generator run in Starlette's threadpool so large captures never buffer fully in memory.
- Statistics: `GET /api/captures/{id}/statistics` — aggregates from conversations; query params `bucket_seconds` (snaps to `{1, 10, 30, 60}` seconds) and `metric` (`packets` or `bytes`).
- Analysis (full): `GET /api/captures/{id}/ai` — SSE streaming; aborts if the client disconnects; persists only successful analyses.
- Chat: under `/api/captures/{id}/...` — `GET /threads` lists, `POST /threads` creates, `GET /threads/{tid}` reads with messages, `DELETE /threads/{tid}` removes (cascade), `POST /threads/{tid}/messages` persists the user turn then streams the assistant reply via SSE. Detects client disconnect and persists the partial answer in `finally`. 400 if `LLM_API_KEY` is unset. Thread ownership is enforced via `_get_owned_capture` → `_get_owned_thread` (both filter on `Capture.user_id`).
- Explain selected: `POST /api/captures/{id}/explain` — one-shot SSE explanation of a set of packet indices (`{ indices: [...] }`); streams `explain_packets_stream`. 400 if `LLM_API_KEY` is unset.
- Capture Command Generator: `POST /api/capture-command/generate` — SSE streaming; body `{ prompt, platform: "tcpdump"|"pktmon", capture_id? }`; streams `capture_command_generate_stream` using `TCPDUMP_GEN_SYSTEM_PROMPT` / `PKTMON_GEN_SYSTEM_PROMPT`. 400 if `LLM_API_KEY` is unset.

## Models (`app/models/capture.py`)
- `Capture`: id, user_id, filename, size_bytes, sha256, linktype (default 1), packet_count, status (`CaptureStatus` enum), stored_path, parsed_index_path, created_at. `chat_threads` relationship cascades delete.
- `Conversation`: id, capture_id, proto, src_ip, src_port, dst_ip, dst_port, packet_count, byte_count, fwd_packet_count, fwd_byte_count (forward-direction breakdown), start_ts, end_ts, app_protocol, flags_summary (comma-separated TCP flag names, e.g. `SYN,ACK`), evidence_json (bounded reservoir sample of structured per-packet evidence used by the LLM prompt).
- `Analysis`: id, conversation_id, model, prompt_tokens, completion_tokens, summary_markdown, issues_json, created_at.
- `ChatThread`: id, capture_id (FK cascade, indexed), title (default "New chat", named from the first question), created_at. `messages` relationship ordered by `created_at`, cascades delete.
- `ChatMessage`: id, thread_id (FK cascade, indexed), role ("user"|"assistant"), content (Text), created_at.

## Models (`app/models/user.py`)
- `User`: id, github_id (unique), login, email, name, avatar_url, created_at.

## Pcap Parser (`app/services/pcap_parser.py`)
- `parse_pcap(capture_id)` — background task, offloaded via `asyncio.to_thread`.
- Uses `scapy.utils.PcapReader` (streaming).
- Writes four sidecars per capture: `capture_id.jsonl` (full per-packet records), `capture_id.summary.jsonl` (compact summaries for list/filter/export), `capture_id.offsets.bin` (binary `<QQ` offset pairs: jsonl byte offset + summary byte offset, 16 bytes/packet, for O(1) random access), and `capture_id.index.json` (metadata: total, linktype, file names).
- Calls `build_conversations()` from `app/services/flows.py`; also collects a bounded reservoir sample of structured per-packet evidence into `Conversation.evidence_json`.
- Updates capture status: uploaded -> parsing -> ready/failed.
- Application protocol detection is centralized here (`_TCP_PORT_PROTOCOLS`, `_UDP_PORT_PROTOCOLS`) and mirrors `wiki/Uploading-and-Analyzing.md`.

## Follow Stream (`app/services/follow.py`)
- `follow_stream_sync(stored_path, proto, src_ip, src_port, dst_ip, dst_port, max_bytes=1MB)` — re-reads the pcap with `PcapReader`, matches packets by canonical 5-tuple, base64-encodes payloads, splits by direction (client = requested src endpoint, server = reverse). Caps each direction at `max_bytes` and sets `truncated=True` when exceeded. Callers offload via `asyncio.to_thread`. Imports `_canonical_key` and `raw_payload_length` from `pcap_parser`.

## LLM Service (`app/services/llm.py`)
- `_get_client()` returns an `AsyncOpenAI(base_url, api_key)`.
- `analyze_conversation(capture, conversation)` — non-streaming, builds a prompt from conversation metadata + `evidence_json`, parses the JSON response (`_extract_json_object` handles fenced blocks), normalizes summary/issues (`_normalize_issues` clamps severity to the documented enum, drops non-object items). Raises on API error so the SSE handler decides whether to record a failure row.
- `chat_stream(context, history, question)` — streaming async generator; system prompt scopes the assistant to the capture and tells it to decline off-topic questions; sends history (user/assistant turns only) then the current question; yields text deltas.
- `explain_packets_stream(capture, packets)` — streaming async generator; builds a prompt from the selected packets' summaries/layer trees and yields a plain-text explanation as deltas. Used by `POST /api/captures/{id}/explain`.
- `capture_command_generate_stream(prompt, platform, capture=None)` — streaming async generator; uses `TCPDUMP_GEN_SYSTEM_PROMPT` or `PKTMON_GEN_SYSTEM_PROMPT` (per platform), optionally injects capture context, and yields a tcpdump/pktmon command as deltas. Used by `POST /api/capture-command/generate`.

## Packet Fields (`app/services/packet_fields.py`)
- `extract_layer_fields(layer)` — Wireshark-style per-field rows (`name`, `value`, `offset`, `length`) for a single scapy layer; `i2repr` with `str(raw_val)` fallback on error.
- `packet_from_raw_hex(raw_hex, linktype=1)` — O(1) reconstruction of a single scapy packet from its stored hex dump + the capture link type (mirrors `PcapReader`'s `conf.l2types.num2layer` mapping). For known linktypes (Ethernet, Raw IP, Linux SLL, etc.) returns `None` when dissection produces only a `Raw` layer, signalling callers to fall back to `read_packet_at()`. For unknown linktypes, falls back to `Raw`. Returns `None` on missing/invalid hex or dissection failure.
- `read_packet_at(stored_path, idx)` — O(idx) fallback that re-opens the pcap and scans from packet 0; used only when `packet_from_raw_hex` returns `None`.
- `enrich_layers_with_fields(record_layers, pkt)` — walks the JSONL layer tree and the scapy payload chain in parallel, attaching `fields` to each node by position; logs a debug-level guard when the layer counts diverge so fields never silently attach to the wrong node.

## Packet Index Cache (`app/api/packets.py`)
- `packets.py` keeps an in-memory LRU cache of parsed `index.json` files keyed by `(path, mtime_ns, size)`.
- A separate byte-bounded LRU (`_FILTER_CACHE`, 64 MB cap) caches proto/`q`-filtered packet index arrays (`array.array("I")`) keyed by `(offsets_path, mtime_ns, size, proto, q)`. The filtered scan runs in a worker thread (`asyncio.to_thread`).
- `_evict_index(index_path)` drops both the index cache entries AND the matching offsets-keyed filter cache entries; called on capture deletion so re-uploads never surface stale data.

## Startup Recovery (`app/main.py`)
- On startup `_reset_stuck_captures()` flips any capture still in `parsing` status to `failed`, because FastAPI BackgroundTasks do not survive a worker restart.

## Settings (`app/config.py`)
- Pydantic `BaseSettings` with `.env` file support, `extra="ignore"`.
- Security knobs: `dev_mode` (relaxes secret validation; never in production), `cookie_secure` (default true), `session_secret` (fallback to JWT_SECRET in dev), `jwt_expire_minutes`.
- Insecure defaults (`CHANGE_ME`, empty, etc.) raise on startup unless `dev_mode=true`.

## Standalone Frontend Serving (`app/main.py`)
- When `SERVE_FRONTEND=true` and `FRONTEND_DIR` (default `/app/frontend-dist`) exists, the built SPA is mounted via `StaticFiles(directory=_FRONTEND_DIR, html=True)` at `/`.
- API/auth routes take priority.

## Key Dependencies
```
fastapi, uvicorn, sqlalchemy[asyncio], asyncpg, alembic, pydantic-settings
scapy, python-jose[cryptography], authlib, httpx, openai, python-multipart,
aiofiles, itsdangerous, psycopg2-binary
```
